<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5605] Go client middleware has no (easy) access to IDL exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5605</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5527&quot; title=&quot;Compiler generated Process function in go will swallow exceptions defined in thrift IDL&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-5527&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-5527&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this is the issue on the client side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But unlike &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5527&quot; title=&quot;Compiler generated Process function in go will swallow exceptions defined in thrift IDL&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-5527&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-5527&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this cannot be resolved by a fix on the compiler code. We managed to write a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/reddit/baseplate.go/blob/e34b108af09beab61f33126dfacf075ff58f5116/thriftbp/client_middlewares.go#L404-L443&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;reflect based helper function&lt;/a&gt; to extract the IDL exceptions out of the result TStruct, I think upstream that helper function to be a provided ClientMiddleware would be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
